DevOps Project: React Application Deployment with CI/CD & Monitoring:

Project Overview:
--> This project demonstrates end-to-end deployment of a production-ready React application using DevOps practices.

It includes:
- Docker containerization
- CI/CD pipeline using Jenkins
- Deployment on AWS EC2
- Monitoring using Prometheus & Grafana


:::::::::::::::::::::::Architecture::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
Application Flow:
GitHub → Jenkins → Docker Build → Docker Hub → EC2 Deployment → Monitoring

Tech Stack:
Frontend: React (Static Build)
Containerization: Docker, Docker Compose
CI/CD: Jenkins
Cloud: AWS EC2
Monitoring: Prometheus, Grafana, Node Exporter, Blackbox Exporter
Version Control: Git & GitHub


devops-build/
│── build/
│── Dockerfile
│── docker-compose.yml
│── build.sh
│── deploy.sh
│── .gitignore
│── .dockerignore
│
├── monitoring/
│   ├── docker-compose.yml
│   ├── prometheus.yml
│   ├── alert.rules.yml


:::::::::::::::::::::::::Docker Setup:::::::::::::::::::::::
Build Image
docker build -t mydockerimage31/dev:latest .

Run Container
docker run -d -p 80:80 --name react-app mydockerimage31/dev:latest


:::::::::::::::::::::::::Bash Automation::::::::::::::::::::::
build.sh
Builds Docker image
Pushes to Docker Hub

deploy.sh
Pulls latest image
Stops old container
Deploys new container


:::::::::::::::AWS DeploymentL:::::::::::::::::
EC2 Instance (Ubuntu)
Ports Open:
22 (SSH - My IP)
80 (HTTP - Public)
8080 (Jenkins)
3000 (Grafana)
9090 (Prometheus)
3001 (Monitoring)


:::::::::::::::::::CI/CD Pipeline (Jenkins)::::::::::::::::::::::
Workflow:
Code pushed to GitHub
Webhook triggers Jenkins
Jenkins:
Builds Docker image
Pushes to Docker Hub
Deploys container on EC2


::::::::::::::::::::::Docker Hub:::::::::::::::::::
Dev Repo (Public): mydockerimage31/dev
Prod Repo (Private): mydockerimage31/prod


:::::::Monitoring Setup:::::::
Tools Used:
Prometheus
Grafana
Node Exporter
Blackbox Exporter

Monitoring Features:
Server metrics (CPU, Memory)
Application uptime monitoring
Alert when application goes down


::::::::::::::::Alerting::::::::::::::::
Prometheus alert rules configured
Detects when application is DOWN


:::::::::::::::::Access URLs:::::::::::::::::::
Application: http://
Jenkins: http://:8080
Grafana: http://:3000
Prometheus: http://:9090


"I deployed a production-ready React application using Docker and Nginx on AWS EC2. I implemented a Jenkins CI/CD pipeline integrated with GitHub webhooks to automate build and deployment. For monitoring, I used Prometheus, Grafana, Node Exporter, and Blackbox Exporter to track both system and application health with alerting configured for downtime detection."
